I finally took the plunge and switched to emacs about a year ago ... 

currently getting myself familiar with elisp so i can enhance my org-mode usage as a fancy todo manager,
and here is the initial version of that small add-on ... be gentle is my first lisp code and my first shot at extending emacs 

https://github.com/gyordanov/smart-todo.el
all it does it speeds up adding todos based on the current buffer path, with a easy way to set due date 


